RHash v1.3.8

Usage: rhash [OPTION...] [FILE | -]...
       rhash --printf=<format string> [FILE | -]...

Options:
  -V, --version Print program version and exit.
  -h, --help    Print this help screen.
  -C, --crc32   Calculate CRC32 hash sum.
      --crc32c  Calculate CRC32C hash sum.
      --md4     Calculate MD4 hash sum.
  -M, --md5     Calculate MD5 hash sum.
  -H, --sha1    Calculate SHA1 hash sum.
      --sha224, --sha256, --sha384, --sha512 Calculate SHA2 hash sum.
      --sha3-224, --sha3-256, --sha3-384, --sha3-512 Calculate SHA3 hash sum.
  -T, --tth     Calculate TTH hash sum.
      --btih    Calculate BitTorrent InfoHash hash sum.
  -A, --aich    Calculate AICH hash sum.
  -E, --ed2k    Calculate eDonkey hash sum.
  -L, --ed2k-link  Calculate and print eDonkey link.
      --tiger   Calculate Tiger hash sum.
  -G, --gost12-256 Calculate GOST R 34.11-2012, 256 bit hash sum.
      --gost12-512 Calculate GOST R 34.11-2012, 512 bit hash sum.
      --gost94  Calculate GOST R 34.11-94 hash sum.
      --gost94-cryptopro Calculate GOST R 34.11-94 CryptoPro hash sum.
      --ripemd160  Calculate RIPEMD-160 hash sum.
      --has160  Calculate HAS-160 hash sum.
      --edonr256, --edonr512  Calculate EDON-R 256/512 hash sum.
      --snefru128, --snefru256  Calculate SNEFRU-128/256 hash sum.
  -a, --all     Calculate all supported hashes.
  -c, --check   Check hash files specified by command line.
  -u, --update  Update hash files specified by command line.
  -e, --embed-crc  Rename files by inserting crc32 sum into name.
  -k, --check-embedded  Verify files by crc32 sum embedded in their names.
      --list-hashes  List the names of supported hashes, one per line.
  -B, --benchmark  Benchmark selected algorithm.
  -v, --verbose Be verbose.
  -r, --recursive  Process directories recursively.
      --file-list=<file> Process a list of files.
  -m, --message=<text> Process the text message.
      --skip-ok Don't print OK messages for successfully verified files.
  -i, --ignore-case  Ignore case of filenames when updating hash files.
      --percents   Show percents, while calculating or checking hashes.
      --speed   Output per-file and total processing speed.
      --maxdepth=<n> Descend at most <n> levels of directories.
  -o, --output=<file> File to output calculation or checking results.
  -l, --log=<file>    File to log errors and verbose information.
      --sfv     Print hash sums, using SFV format (default).
      --bsd     Print hash sums, using BSD-like format.
      --simple  Print hash sums, using simple format.
  -g, --magnet  Print hash sums  as magnet links.
      --torrent Create torrent files.
      --template=<file> Load a printf-like template from the <file>
  -p, --printf=<format string>  Format and print hash sums.
                See the RHash manual for details.
